cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CC 

This paper deals with network coding and interference alignment techniques, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper also discusses graph-related properties and degree-counting techniques, which are relevant to the fields of graph theory (cs.DC) and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for checking the feasibility of PBNA, which could be considered a system implementation or optimization problem and thus falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
